   237	5. User can remove individual doses from the batch before confirming (e.g., skip one compound)
   238	6. Success: dashboard clears all logged doses; total time target ≤ 3 taps
   239	
   240	**Log record fields:**
   241	- Protocol reference (FK)
   242	- Actual dose taken (may differ from scheduled amount)
   243	- Timestamp (auto-captured; editable within same calendar day only)
   244	- Injection site used
   245	- Note (optional)
   246	- Logged by (user ID — relevant for admin visibility)
   247	
   248	**Error scenarios:**
   249	- User attempts to log a dose when vial inventory shows 0 remaining → warning ("No active vial recorded for this compound — log anyway?"); does not block, but flags prominently
   250	- Duplicate log for same protocol + same day → "You already logged this today. Log again?" — requires confirmation
   251	- Missed dose (calendar day passes with no log) → no automatic fill or penalty; appears as "Not logged" in history; retroactive logging not supported after the calendar day ends (audit integrity)
   252	- Dose skip (user intentionally skips) → user can tap "Skip" on a dose entry; recorded as a skip event; counts as 0 in adherence metrics; distinguishable from "Not logged" in history
   253	- Late dose (logged same calendar day but past typical window) → accepted; no time-window enforcement; timestamp is as logged
   254	- Timezone / DST shift → all timestamps stored in UTC; dashboard "today's doses" resolves based on user's browser local date
   255	
   256	#### 5.2.3 Injection Site Rotation
   257	
   258	**Rotation system:**
   259	- Selectable sites: left abdomen, right abdomen, left thigh, right thigh, left deltoid, right deltoid, ventrogluteal L, ventrogluteal R
   260	- Per-compound site history (peptides with route requirements respect the correct site group)

