   400	### 5.4 Pillar 4 — Ordering (Telegram + Crypto)
   401	
   402	**What it does:**
   403	Enables the Power User to place a vendor order via Telegram with the app sending the order message automatically via MTProto (user's own Telegram account). The user then handles crypto payment manually through Coinbase.
   404	
   405	**⚠ v1 architecture decision — supersedes vision guidance:**
   406	The vision document recommended "guided manual v1" (app composes message; user pastes to Telegram). The user has confirmed v1 = full Telegram automation (MTProto sends the message without opening Telegram). This decision elevates Telegram session fragility from a v2 risk to a v1 Must Have risk. As a result, a graceful manual fallback mode (message is copyable; Telegram deep-link is always visible) is **required** in every ordering flow, not optional.
   407	
   408	**External actor — QSC vendor:** The vendor is a key external participant in the ordering flow. v1 assumes QSC's Telegram-first ordering pattern: user sends an item list message → vendor replies with confirmed price and wallet address. Vendor reply format is unstructured; v1 processes vendor replies manually. The v2 AI response parser adds automated reply extraction.
   409	
   410	**MTProto feasibility gate:** Before Phase 1 ships, validate in the target runtime: (a) MTProto auth code flow completes successfully, (b) session storage and retrieval is reliable across restarts, (c) message send to a real vendor chat succeeds. If a blocker is found, fall back to "compose only" scope reduction — app writes the message, user copies it to Telegram — without shipping Phase 1 incomplete.
   411	
   412	#### 5.4.1 Telegram Account Authentication (one-time setup)
   413	
   414	**Setup flow:**
   415	1. User enters their Telegram phone number
   416	2. Telegram sends a verification code via standard MTProto auth
   417	3. User enters code in app
   418	4. App stores encrypted MTProto session (server-side, AES-256 at rest, user-scoped)
   419	5. User selects or enters the vendor's Telegram username / chat ID
   420	6. App sends a test "ping" message (or skips — user discretion) to confirm connection
   421	
   422	**Vendor configuration per vendor:**
   423	- Vendor display name
   424	- Telegram username or chat ID
   425	- Order message template (plain text with item/quantity placeholders; default provided)
   426	- Preferred currency (USDT, BTC, ETH, etc.)
   427	
   428	**Fallback always visible:**
   429	- Composed order message is always shown as copyable text in the UI
   430	- "Open in Telegram" deep-link button (tg://resolve?domain=VENDOR&text=MESSAGE) always present
   431	- User can always choose to send manually even when automation is configured
   432	
   433	**Out of scope:** Official Telegram Bot API (bots can't initiate messages to arbitrary users); OAuth (no standard OAuth for Telegram user accounts)
   434	
   435	**Error scenarios:**
   436	- Auth code expired → re-request code flow with timer
   437	- Session invalidated by Telegram (device limit) → force re-auth with clear explanation: "Your Telegram session was invalidated. Re-authenticate to resume ordering."
   438	- Vendor username not found → inline error + show manual fallback immediately
