   454	
   455	#### 5.4.2b Inventory-Aware Order Suggestions (Must Have)
   456	
   457	When the user opens the order builder, the app calculates days-to-depletion for each active protocol's compound and surfaces a "Suggested order" section at the top of the order builder.
   458	
   459	**Suggestion logic:**
   460	- For each active protocol: estimated daily dose rate × doses remaining in active vial = days until depletion
   461	- If days until depletion < 14: show compound in suggested list with: compound name, vial form + size currently used, days remaining, suggested reorder quantity (default: 2 vials)
   462	- Compounds with no active vial record but active protocol → also surfaced: "No active vial recorded"
   463	
   464	**Suggested order UI:**
   465	- Shown as a collapsible section "Based on your inventory" above the full vendor catalog
   466	- Each suggested item has: compound name, reason ("~8 doses remaining"), pre-filled quantity (editable), "Add to cart" button
   467	- Dismissible per session if user prefers to browse manually
   468	
   469	**Out of scope:** ML-based quantity optimization, multi-cycle lookahead beyond 14 days
   470	
   471	#### 5.4.3 Order Builder
   472	
   473	**Order flow:**
   474	1. Browse or search vendor catalog
   475	2. Add items to cart (compound, form, vial size, quantity)
   476	3. Review cart: itemized list with per-item price, subtotal
   477	4. App composes the Telegram order message using vendor's template (e.g., "Hi, I'd like to order: 10x BPC-157 5mg, 5x TB-500 5mg. Please confirm price and wallet address. Thank you.")
   478	5. User reviews composed message (editable before send)
   479	6. User clicks "Send Order" → app sends message via Telegram MTProto to vendor chat
   480	7. App records the order with status: "Sent — awaiting confirmation" and timestamps the event
   481	
   482	**Order record fields (created at send):**
   483	- Order ID, created timestamp
   484	- Vendor reference
   485	- Line items: compound, form, vial size, quantity, unit price
   486	- Telegram message text (as sent)
   487	- Order status (see state machine in §5.4.4)
   488	- `send_method`: `"automated"` (MTProto send succeeded) | `"manual_fallback"` (user used copy/deep-link)
   489	- Payment fields (populated in §5.4.4): confirmed total, currency, wallet address, tx ID (optional)
   490	
   491	**Duplicate item in cart:** If the same compound + form + vial size is added more than once, quantities are merged into one line item. Different vial sizes of the same compound are separate line items.
   492	
   493	**Fallback mode (always available, even when bot is working):**
   494	- Composed message visible as copyable text below the send button
   495	- "Open in Telegram" deep-link button visible at all times
   496	- If MTProto send fails for any reason → show error, automatically surface fallback mode, do NOT silently discard the order
   497	
   498	**Out of scope:** Discount codes or promo fields, multi-vendor split orders
   499	
   500	**Error scenarios:**
   501	- Telegram send fails (network, session expired, rate limit) → show error message + fallback mode immediately; order remains in "draft" state
   502	- Cart is empty → send button disabled; "Add items to your order first"
   503	- Item in cart has no price set → soft warning: "Price not set for [item]. Order will be sent without a price confirmation."
   504	
   505	#### 5.4.4 Order Tracking & Payment
   506	
   507	**Post-send flow:**
   508	1. App shows "Order sent — waiting for vendor confirmation" with Telegram deep-link to vendor chat
   509	2. User reads vendor's Telegram reply manually (v1; AI response parser is v2)
   510	3. User manually enters in app: confirmed order total, crypto currency, wallet address from vendor's message
   511	4. App shows payment confirmation step: total, currency, wallet address — all visible together on one screen
   512	5. **User must acknowledge the wallet address + amount display before proceeding** (safety gate)
   513	6. User sends crypto payment from Coinbase or other wallet manually (app does not execute payment)
   514	7. User optionally enters transaction ID in app (for audit record)
   515	8. User clicks "Mark payment sent" → order status: "Payment sent — awaiting shipment"
   516	9. User receives shipment; clicks "Mark received" → triggers inventory update prompt
   517	10. App prompts: "Add these items to your inventory?" with each ordered compound and quantity pre-filled
   518	
   519	**Payment safety guardrail:**
   520	The wallet address and payment amount must be visible on screen at the moment the user clicks "Mark payment sent." This step cannot be bypassed. If no wallet address has been entered, the "Mark payment sent" button is greyed with tooltip: "Enter vendor's wallet address first."

