   799	|-------------|--------|
   800	| v1 user target | 1–50 users (personal + family/friends) |
   801	| Architecture | Stateless API; single server sufficient at v1 scale; horizontal scale viable without rearchitecting |
   802	| DB growth | < 1 GB Year 1; archive dose logs > 2 years old to cold storage if needed |
   803	| Telegram sessions | 1 active session (Power User only; ordering is single-user in v1) |
   804	| Concurrent users | Support 10 simultaneous authenticated sessions without degradation at v1 scale |
   805	
   806	### 8.4 Availability
   807	
   808	| Requirement | Target |
   809	|-------------|--------|
   810	| Uptime | 99% monthly (7.3 hours downtime/month acceptable for a personal tool) |
   811	| Deploy strategy | Zero-downtime deploys via rolling update preferred |
   812	| Backup | Daily automated DB backup; 30-day retention |
   813	| RTO | 4 hours (personal tool; no SLA required) |
   814	| RPO | 24 hours (last day's data at risk in worst-case total failure) |
   815	| Failure behavior | If API is unreachable, dose log flow degrades to "offline pending" if technically feasible; otherwise shows clear "service unavailable" with no data loss |
   816	
   817	### 8.5 Accessibility
   818	
   819	- **Target:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for all pages accessible to Delegated Participants (dose logging, dashboard, reference pages)
   820	- **Rationale:** Managed users may include older family members; basic accessibility ensures usability
   821	- **Admin panel:** Best-effort; keyboard navigable; full WCAG compliance not required for v1
   822	- **Testing:** axe automated scan on every CI build; manual keyboard navigation check on critical flows (dose logging, reconstitution calculator)
   823	
   824	### 8.6 Browser & Device Support
   825	
   826	| Tier | Scope | Commitment |
   827	|------|-------|------------|
   828	| **Supported** | Chrome (last 2), Safari (last 2), Firefox (last 2), Edge (last 2), Chrome for Android, Safari iOS (last 2) | All features work; regressions are P0 |
   829	| **Unsupported** | IE 11, Safari < 14 | May not function; no engineering effort |
   830	
   831	**Mobile priority:** The dose-logging flow is used on a phone at 7am. Dashboard + dose logging must be first-class on mobile. Reference pages and admin panel can be desktop-first with responsive fallback.
   832	
   833	**PWA requirements (Must Have):**
   834	- PWA manifest: app name, icons (192px, 512px), theme color, `display: standalone`
   835	- Home screen install prompt: browser "Add to Home Screen" on mobile Chrome and Safari iOS
   836	- Installed PWA: opens full-screen without browser chrome; back/forward navigation handled in-app
   837	- Service worker: caches app shell for fast load; queues dose-log writes when offline and syncs on reconnection
   838	- Offline behavior: dose logging works offline (queued writes); all other features show "offline" state gracefully
   839	- Push notification support: Web Push API for dose reminders (§5.2.7); requires notification permission grant
   840	
   841	### 8.7 Monitoring & Observability
   842	
   843	For a solo developer who is also the operator, application monitoring is operationally necessary to detect silent failures.
   844	
   845	| Requirement | Target |
   846	|-------------|--------|
   847	| Application error tracking | Unhandled server errors logged and surfaced; P0 errors (reconstitution math failure, payment flow error, audit write failure) alerted within 15 minutes |
   848	| Telegram send failure | Failed MTProto sends surfaced in order history with error state; no silent discard |
   849	| Uptime monitoring | External uptime check (e.g., Uptime Robot or equivalent); alert if unreachable > 5 minutes |
   850	| Backup verification | Daily backup completion logged; alert on backup failure |
   851	| Audit log integrity | DB assertion in integration tests that audit events are written; alert if audit write fails silently |
   852	
   853	Specific tooling is a tech-stack decision. All monitoring tooling must fall within the §7.3 infrastructure budget.
   854	
   855	### 8.8 Internationalization
   856	
   857	**v1 scope:** English only. US locale only.
   858	- Date format: MM/DD/YYYY (user-facing); ISO 8601 in UTC stored in DB
   859	- Timezone: all timestamps stored in UTC; displayed in user's local browser timezone
   860	- Currency: USD for vendor price catalog display; crypto labels shown as-is (USDT, BTC, ETH)
   861	- Units: metric throughout (mcg, mg, mL, IU)
   862	- i18n/l10n framework not required for v1. Re-evaluate at public launch (Year 2) if European users are targeted.
   863	
   864	---
   865	
   866	## 9. Competitive Context
   867	
   868	*(Full competitive analysis in `docs/vision.md` §6. PRD summary only.)*
   869	
   870	**Why competitors cannot build what we're building:**
   871	- App-Store-bound trackers (PeptIQ, Smart Peptide Tracker, Titer, Peptify, SHOTLOG) structurally cannot integrate grey-market Telegram/crypto ordering. The ordering → inventory → dose data loop is our structural moat regardless of automation level.
   872	- PeptPro (web, closest feature surface) uses their own curated vendor marketplace — not grey-market Telegram. They serve a fundamentally different user.
   873	- No competitor closes the order → inventory → dose → outcome data loop.
   874	
   875	**Features to learn from:**
   876	- **PeptIQ:** injection site rotation UX (reportedly polished); reference their interaction pattern
   877	- **Titer:** row-level security + CSV export as a privacy baseline; match their data controls
   878	- **Peptify:** pharmacokinetic modeling as a v2+ signal; not v1 scope but worth designing a data model compatible with it
   879	- **PeptPro:** wearable integration (Oura/Whoop) as a v2 biomarker signal; same reasoning
   880	
   881	---
   882	
   883	## 10. Phased Delivery Plan
   884	
   885	> **Phase vs. MoSCoW alignment:** The MoSCoW table (§4) lists all features that must be complete before v1 is declared done. Phases below define build order — Must Have features are delivered across Phase 1 and Phase 2 in sequence, not all at once. V1 is "complete" when all Must Have and prioritized Should Have items have shipped.
   886	
   887	### Phase 1 — Personal Tool (M0–M3)
   888	
   889	**Goal:** Power User decommissions spreadsheet within 90 days. Places first order via app.
   890	
   891	**Deliverables:**
   892	1. Auth (email/password, accounts, sessions, password reset)
   893	2. Compound reference pages (~20–30 from QSC catalog)
   894	3. Protocol creation + daily dose logging (no injection site rotation yet)
   895	4. Reconstitution calculator + vial inventory
   896	5. Telegram MTProto auth + order builder + automated send + manual fallback
   897	6. Basic order history and payment tracking
   898	
   899	**Phase gate:** Power User logs doses every day for 14 consecutive days AND places 1 successful Telegram order via app.
   900	
   901	> **Note on data export:** Account deletion with full data export (§5.7) is implemented in Phase 1 as part of Auth, even though the export-on-demand settings UI is refined in Phase 3. Phase 1 ships: account deletion + full JSON export generated at deletion time. Phase 3 adds: "Export my data" button in account settings at any time.
   902	
   903	---
   904	
   905	### Phase 2 — Family Adoption (M3–M6)
   906	
   907	**Goal:** First Delegated Participants active and logging reliably.
   908	
   909	**Deliverables:**
   910	1. Multi-user system: admin panel, managed user invitation, simplified managed-user view
   911	2. Injection site rotation tracking
   912	3. Cycle management
   913	4. Subjective outcome logging
   914	5. Stack overview dashboard
   915	6. Coinbase payment checklist (guided payment details capture)
   916	7. Mobile-responsive polish on dose-logging and dashboard flows
   917	
   918	**Phase gate:** 3+ Delegated Participants with active protocols, logging ≥ 5 days/week for 30 days.
   919	
   920	> **Legal gate:** Before Phase 2 ships, complete the Phase 2 legal review (see §7.5) covering managed user data stewardship obligations.
   921	
   922	---
   923	
   924	### Phase 3 — Hardening + v2 Bets (M6–M12)
   925	
   926	**Goal:** Validate personal-tool adoption. Begin v2 technology differentiators. Prepare for potential paid license.
   927	
   928	**Deliverables:**
   929	1. Protocol history view and cycle analytics (simple charts)
   930	2. Data export (JSON) and full account deletion
   931	3. AI Telegram response parser (v2 feature: reads vendor confirmation, auto-captures wallet address + total)
   932	4. Automated PubMed watch (background job, email digest of new papers on stack compounds)
   933	5. Legal review (required before paid license consideration)
   934	6. Evaluate: lab data import / bloodwork correlation (v2 feasibility spike)
   935	
   936	**Phase gate:** 20 successful orders total; Delegated Participant 7-day adherence ≥ 70%; legal review completed.
   937	
   938	---
   939	
   940	### Year 2+ Aspirations
   941	
   942	| Feature | Dependency |
   943	|---------|-----------|
   944	| Paid lifetime license | Legal review passed |
   945	| Compounding pharmacy order flow | Bridge-sourcing UX (architecture ready) |
   946	| TRT/anabolic compound profiles | Compound profile schema already supports it |
   947	| Lab data import + protocol-biomarker correlation | v2 feasibility spike from Phase 3 |
   948	| Public reference site (SEO) | Personal-tool adoption validates content investment |
   949	| Community features (opt-in, low-noise) | Year 2 only if personal-tool succeeds |
   950	
   951	---
   952	
   953	## 11. Risk Assessment
   954	
   955	| Risk | Severity | Probability | Mitigation |
   956	|------|----------|-------------|------------|
   957	| Telegram MTProto session fragility (v1 critical path) | HIGH | MEDIUM | Graceful manual fallback in every ordering flow; explicit error states; session re-auth flow |
   958	| Power User abandons the build before family adoption | HIGH | MEDIUM | Personal-tool-first phasing; M1 deliverables benefit Power User immediately. If no daily use after 30 days, pause and reassess. |
   959	| Payment processor rejects paid license | HIGH | MEDIUM | Legal review before any paid launch. Base product = tracker/reference honestly described. Ordering = opt-in advanced module. |
   960	| Telegram MTProto terms of service | MEDIUM | LOW | MTProto is a standard protocol; third-party clients are widespread. Single-user, single-vendor use is a normal personal use case. No mass-messaging. |
   961	| Grey-market regulatory crackdown | MEDIUM | LOW | Sourcing module is architecturally isolatable. Bridge-sourcing design supports compounding pharmacy as an alternative from day one. |
   962	| Legal exposure (grey-market ordering facilitation) | MEDIUM | LOW | Legal review before paid launch. Harm-reduction framing throughout. The user places the order; the app composes and sends the message on their behalf. |
   963	| Managed user non-adoption | LOW | HIGH | Don't force adoption. Track usage. Only invest in managed-user UX that real managed users request. |
   964	| Reference content quality decay | LOW | MEDIUM | Every profile cites primary sources; anecdote is labeled. AI drafts are human-reviewed before publish. |
   965	
   966	---
   967	
   968	## 12. Open Questions Resolved
   969	
   970	| Source | Question | Decision |
   971	|--------|----------|----------|
   972	| Vision Q2 | Platform shape | Web app (multi-tenant, user accounts, no App Store) |
   973	| Vision Q4 | Telegram automation scope (v1 vs. v2) | **v1 = full MTProto automation** (supersedes vision's guided-manual guidance); graceful manual fallback required |
   974	| Vision Q5 | Multi-user architecture | Distinct accounts; Power User = super admin; managed users see own data only |
   975	| Vision Q8 | Vendor sourcing scope | QSC-first for v1; architecture supports N vendors; v2 adds more |
   976	| Vision Q9 | Legal review trigger | **Before paid license launch**; family/friend use is free until then |
   977	| PRD discovery | Reference catalog depth | QSC catalog only (~20–30 compounds) for v1 |
   978	| PRD discovery | Tracker v1 features | All four confirmed as Must Have: dose logging, injection site rotation, cycle management, subjective outcome logging |
   979	
   980	**Still open (tech-stack step):**
   981	- Q3 — Database + deployment technology choices
   982	- Q10 — AI assistance technical approach (vector search? OpenAI? Local model?)
   983	
   984	**Still open (later):**
   985	- Q1 — Product name
   986	- Q6 — Public reference site timing
   987	- Q7 — Community features scope
   988	
